      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "Hi, we have run the pre -check  https://github.com/wafer-space/gf180mcu-precheck for our filled gds. We don't have any DRC error in Klayout, but we have two types of Magic DRC errors. May I ask are those waviable? \nThe MAGIC DRC errors are: **This layer can't abut or partially overlap between subcells** and  **p-ohmic spacing to NMOS gate < 0.33um (PP.4b + NP.4c)**\nAny help will be appreciated, thanks!",
