      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2025-12-11T01:13:10.036+00:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "Actually after re-reading the NP and PP rules again, I'm pretty sure the rule in magic is just bogus.  I think in one place I misinterpreted a spacing to NCOMP as a spacing to NPLUS;  consequently the rule is flagging an error at a distance of less than 0.33um when the actual minimum distance appears to be 0.32um.   The fact that it is off by only 10nm is why it hasn't come up before.",
